        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 24 at 6:15AM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 615 AM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm 4 miles
southwest of Hanna, moving east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation
is possible.

Locations in or near the path include...
Hanna...                          Indianola...
Vernon...                         Crowder...
Canadian...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1000 AM CDT for
southeastern Oklahoma.</instruction>
